Therefore the straight line BC is not in a more elevated plane;
             therefore the three straight lines BC , BD ,
               BE are in one plane.

For let NK , DH be produced and meet one
             another at R , and further let FM , GE be produced to P , Q ;
             let AO , LP , CQ , BR be joined.

But the solids DX , BT and the solids DC , BA have the same heights respectively;
             therefore, as the base EH is to the base NQ
             , so is the height of the solid DC to the height of the solid AB .
